<h1>Problem 1180 - 1987 IMO, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>In an acute-angled triangle \(ABC\) the interior bisector of angle \(A\) meets \(BC\) at \(L\) and meets the circumcircle of \(ABC\) again at \(N\). From \(L\) perpendiculars are drawn to \(AB\) and \(AC\), with feet \(K\) and \(M\) respectively. Prove that the quadrilateral \(AKNM\) and the triangle \(ABC\) have equal areas.</p>
